file_summary: This file serves as a .gitignore configuration, defining patterns for files and directories that Git should ignore when tracking changes in a repository. Its primary purpose is to prevent temporary files, build artifacts, IDE-specific configuration files, and other generated content from being committed to the version control system. This helps keep the repository clean, ensures consistency across different developer environments, and reduces the size of the repository. The file includes comprehensive ignore rules for common development tools and environments such as Maven (target/ directories, pom.xml.bak), Gradle (build/ directories), various Integrated Development Environments like Spring Tool Suite (STS), IntelliJ IDEA, NetBeans, and Visual Studio Code (VS Code), as well as SDK Man related files and specific CSS build outputs like `_site/` and generated `.css` files, while explicitly keeping `petclinic.css`.
